commitResults.messageTitle: > Gave chatbot a new name (Eva), to differentiate it from the placeholder name Duke > Changed the ASCII Logo to Eva's > Implemented an initial skeletal version such that it simply greets the user and exits > Removed the initial Duke.java file
> Improved the skeletal version of Duke so that it echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types the command bye.
> Added the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested. > Assumed there will be no more than 100 tasks
> Added the ability to mark tasks as done and to change the status back to not done. > Used a Task class to represent tasks.

> Added  support for tracking three types of tasks: > ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it e.g., visit new theme park > Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time e.g., submit report by 11/10/2019 5pm > Events: tasks that start at a specific date/time and ends at a specific date/time e.g., (a) team project meeting 2/10/2019 2-4pm (b) orientation week 4/10/2019 to 11/10/2019
commitResults.messageBody: > Used Inheritance to support multiple task types

commitResults.messageTitle: > Used the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Duke.
> Taught the chatbot to deal with errors such as incorrect inputs entered by the user. > Used exceptions to handle errors
> Added support for deleting tasks from the list. > Used ArrayList<Task> to store tasks.
> Used Java Enums > Added Javadoc comments where necessary
> Cleaned up the formatting
